rs List |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-country/2019-cmt-music-awards-winners-list-844075/ |website=Rolling Stone |accessdate=20 July 2019 |date=6 June 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Country Music Association Awards]]\n| New Artist of the Year\n| Himself\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>{{Cite web |url=https://abcnews.go.com/GMA/Culture/2019-cma-awards-complete-winners-list/story?id=66949919 |title=Archived copy |access-date=2019-11-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191115015928/https://abcnews.go.com/GMA/Culture/2019-cma-awards-complete-winners-list/story?id=66949919 |archive-date=2019-11-15 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n!2020\n| [[Academy of Country Music Awards]]\n| New Male Artist of the Year\n| Himself\n| {{pending}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://theboot.com/2020-acm-awards-nominees-list/ |title=2020 ACM Awards: The Nominees List |website=Theboot.com |date= |accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Tours ==\n===Headlining===\n* If I Know Me Tour (2019)\n* [[Monster Energy]] presents Whiskey Glasses Roadshow (2020)\n\n=== Supporting ===\n* [[Dig Your Roots Tour]] (2016) with [[Florida Georgia Line]]\n* [[Smooth Tour]] (2017) with Florida Georgia Line\n* [[Can't Say I Ain't Country Tour]] (2019) with Florida Georgia Line\n* Beer Never Broke My Heart Tour (2019) with [[Luke Combs]]\n* We Back Tour (2020) with [[Jason Aldean]]\n*[[Proud to Be Right Here Tour]] (2020) with [[Luke Bryan]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://morganwallen.com/ Official website]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wallen, Morgan}}\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:American male singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:American country singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Country musicians from Tennessee]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Hancock County, Tennessee]]\n[[Category:The Voice (franchise) contestants]]\n[[Category:Big Loud Records artists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American country music singer and songwriter}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Morgan Wallen\n| image            = \n| image_size       = \n| landscape        = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank -->\n| alt              = \n| caption          = \n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = Morgan Cole Wallen\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1993|05|13}}\n| birth_place      = [[Sneedville, Tennessee]]\n| origin           = \n| genre            = [[Country music|Country]]\n| occupation       = {{flatlist|\n* Singer\n* songwriter\n}}\n| instrument       = {{flatlist|\n* Vocals\n* guitar\n}}\n| years_active     = 2016\u2013present\n| label            = [[Big Loud Records|Big Loud]]\n| associated_acts  = \n| website          = {{URL|morganwallen.com}}\n}}\n'''Morgan Cole Wallen''' (born May 13, 1993) is an American [[country music]] singer and songwriter. He is signed to [[Big Loud Records]] and has released four singles: \"The Way I Talk\", \"[[Up Down (Morgan Wallen song)|Up Down]]\", which features [[Florida Georgia Line]], \"[[Whiskey Glasses]]\", and his current single \"Chasin' You\".\n\n==Early life==\nWallen was born in [[Sneedville, Tennessee]].<ref name=\"nash\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nashcountrydaily.com/2017/03/13/whos-new-morgan-wallen-2/|title=Who\u2019s New: Morgan Wallen|last=Casey|first=Jim|date=March 13, 2017|work=Nash Country Daily|accessdate=April 23, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170424085547/http://www.nashcountrydaily.com/2017/03/13/whos-new-morgan-wallen-2/|archive-date=April 24, 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> His father was a Baptist pastor and as a child, Wallen took piano and violin lessons. He was offered a scholarship to play baseball in college, but after an injury, chose to pursue music instead.\n\n==Career==\n===2014: ''The Voice''===\nIn 2014, Wallen competed on [[The Voice (U.S. season 6)|season 6]] of ''[[The Voice (U.S. TV series)|The Voice]]'', initially as part of [[Usher (musician)|Usher]]'s team and later [[Adam Levine]]'s team. He was eliminated during the Playoffs.<ref name=\"nash\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; line-height:16px;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Stage\n! scope=\"col\" | Song\n! scope=\"col\" | Original artist\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" | Order\n! scope=\"col\" | Result\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Blind Audition\n| \"[[Collide (Howie Day song)|Collide]]\"\n| [[Howie Day]]\n| March 4, 2014\n| 4.2\n| [[Shakira]] and [[Usher (musician)|Usher]] turned<br />Joined Team Usher\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Battles, Round 1\n| \"[[Hey Brother]]\" <small>(vs. Brothers Walker)</small>\n| [[Avicii]]\n| March 18, 2014\n| 9.5\n| Saved by Coach\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Battles, Round 2\n| \"[[Story of My Life (One Direction song)|Story of My Life]]\" <small>(vs. Stevie Jo)</small>\n| [[One Direction]]\n| April 1, 2014\n| 15.4\n| Defeated<br>Stolen by [[Adam Levine]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Playoffs\n| \"[[Stay (Black Stone Cherry song)|Stay]]\"\n| [[Florida Georgia Line]]\n| April 14, 2014\n| 18.9\n| Eliminated\n|}\n\n===2016\u2013present: Big Loud Records and ''If I Know Me''===\nIn late 2016, Wallen signed to Big Loud Records, a label owned by record producer [[Joey Moi]]. He released his debut single \"The Way I Talk\" soon afterward.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.musicrow.com/2016/09/big-loud-records-morgan-wallen-trades-baseball-ambitions-for-country-music-dreams/|title=Big Loud Records\u2019 Morgan Wallen Trades Baseball Ambitions For Country Music Dreams|last=Nicholson|first=Jessica|date=September 27, 2016|work=[[MusicRow]]|accessdate=April 23, 2017}}</ref> In addition, he co-wrote the [[A Thousand Horses]] single \"Preachin' to the Choir\".<ref name=\"nash\"/> In April 2017, Wallen released a [[music video]] for \"The Way I Talk\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soundslikenashville.com/news/morgan-wallen-celebrates-upbringing-video-way-talk/|title=Morgan Wallen Celebrates Upbringing in Video for \u2018The Way I Talk\u2019|last=Brickey|first=Kelly|date=April 9, 2017|work=Sounds Like Nashville|accessdate=April 23, 2017}}</ref> He also joined [[Florida Georgia Line]] for set dates on their ''[[Dig Your Roots Tour]]''.<ref name=\"nash\"/>\n\nOn April 27, 2018, Wallen released his debut album, ''[[If I Know Me (album)|If I Know Me]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.radio.com/blogs/lauren-hoffman/exclusive-morgan-wallens-debut-album-if-i-know-me-reveals-what-hes-all-about |title=EXCLUSIVE: Morgan Wallen's Debut Album 'If I Know Me' Reveals What He's All About|date=April 26, 2018|first=Lauren |last= Hoffman |work=Radio.com }}</ref><ref>Jon Freeman, (June 19, 2018) [https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-country/how-up-down-singer-morgan-wallen-turned-his-accent-into-an-honest-country-voice-666096/ ''Rolling Stone'']</ref> The second single from the album, \"[[Up Down (Morgan Wallen song)|Up Down]]\", was recorded with Florida Georgia Line.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/country/8289658/morgan-wallen-up-down-hot-100-interview |title=How 'Up Down' Singer Morgan Wallen Went From Singing at Bonfires to Collaborating With Florida Georgia Line |date=April 19, 2018 |first= Tatiana |last=Cirisano }}</ref> According to Wallen, he and Florida Georgia Line got together as they knew each other, and when FGL heard the single, they became interested in a collaboration.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.megacountry.com/videos/14321-morgan-wallen-talks-fgl-collab |title=Morgan Wallen Talks New Single Collab with Florida Georgia Line |work=MegaCountry }}</ref> The album's third single \"[[Whiskey Glasses]]\" released to country radio on July 30, 2018. It reached at number one on the Country Airplay in June 2019. Wallen joined Florida Georgia Line on their [[Can't Say I Ain't Country Tour]] in 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.onecountry.com/country-artists/florida-georgia-line-announce-tour-dates/|title=Florida Georgia Line Announce Can\u2019t Say I Ain\u2019t Country Tour with Dan + Shay|last=Konicki|first=Lisa|date=2019-01-09|website=One Country|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-02}}</ref> Wallen also made a short appearance on the December 3, 2018 episode of [[WWE Raw]]. \"Whiskey Glasses\" went on to become the year-end #1 song on country radio for 2019.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bulletins.billboard.com/country/country_update_1209.pdf|title=Billboard Country Update|date=December 9, 2019|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref> Wallen released \"Chasin' You\" to country radio as the fourth single from ''If I Know Me'' in July 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nashcountrydaily.com/2019/07/09/morgan-wallen-to-release-smoldering-new-single-chasin-you-listen/|title=Morgan Wallen to Release Smoldering New Single, \"Chasin\u2019 You\" [Listen]|last=Casey|first=Jim|website=Nash Country Daily|publisher=Cumulus Media|date=July 9, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://tasteofcountry.com/morgan-wallen-chasin-you-single/|title=Morgan Wallen Is Still After an Ex in New Single \u2018Chasin\u2019 You\u2019 [Listen]|website=Taste of Country|accessdate=January 24, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Details\n! colspan=\"4\"| Peak chart positions\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Sales\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Certifications\n|- style=\"font-size:smaller;\"\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[Billboard 200|US]]<br /><ref name=\"BB200\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/morgan-wallen/chart-history/TLP |title=Morgan Wallen Chart History: Billboard 200 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=January 23, 2020}}</ref>\n! style=\"width:4em;\"| [[Top Country Albums|US Country]]<br /><ref name=\"Country Albums\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/music/morgan-wallen/chart-history/CLP |title=Morgan Wallen Chart History (Top Country Albums) |work=