/www.rollingstone.com/music/music-country/2019-cmt-music-awards-winners-list-844075/ |website=Rolling Stone |accessdate=20 July 2019 |date=6 June 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Country Music Association Awards]]\n| New Artist of the Year\n| Himself\n| {{nom}}\n| <ref>{{Cite web |url=https://abcnews.go.com/GMA/Culture/2019-cma-awards-complete-winners-list/story?id=66949919 |title=Archived copy |access-date=2019-11-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191115015928/https://abcnews.go.com/GMA/Culture/2019-cma-awards-complete-winners-list/story?id=66949919 |archive-date=2019-11-15 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n!2020\n| [[Academy of Country Music Awards]]\n| New Male Artist of the Year\n| Himself\n| {{pending}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://theboot.com/2020-acm-awards-nominees-list/ |title=2020 ACM Awards: The Nominees List |website=Theboot.com |date= |accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Tours ==\n===Headlining===\n* If I Know Me Tour (2019)\n* [[Monster Energy]] presents Whiskey Glasses Roadshow (2020)\n\n=== Supporting ===\n* [[Dig Your Roots Tour]] (2016) with [[Florida Georgia Line]]\n* [[Smooth Tour]] (2017) with Florida Georgia Line\n* [[Can't Say I Ain't Country Tour]] (2019) with Florida Georgia Line\n* Beer Never Broke My Heart Tour (2019) with [[Luke Combs]]\n* We Back Tour (2020) with [[Jason Aldean]]\n*[[Proud to Be Right Here Tour]] (2020) with [[Luke Bryan]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://morganwallen.com/ Official website]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wallen, Morgan}}\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:American male singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:American country singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Country musicians from Tennessee]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Hancock County, Tennessee]]\n[[Category:The Voice (franchise) contestants]]\n[[Category:Big Loud Records artists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n", "name_user": "Ss112", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eStudio albums:updated", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morgan_Wallen"}
{"title_page": "HM Prison Everthorpe", "text_new": "{{Infobox prison\n| prison_name    = HMP Everthorpe\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| location       = [[Everthorpe]], [[East Riding of Yorkshire]]\n| coordinates    = \n| status         = \n| classification = [[Prisoner security categories in the United Kingdom|Adult Male/Category C]]\n| capacity       = \n| population     = 689\n| populationdate = December 2007\n| opened         = 1958\n| closed         = \n| former_name    =\n| managed_by     = [[Her Majesty's Prison Service|HM Prison Services]]\n| governor       = Marcella Goligher\n| website        = {{HM prison|everthorpe|Everthorpe}}\n}}\n'''HM Prison Everthorpe''' was a [[Prison security categories in the United Kingdom|Category C]] men's [[prison]], located to the south-west of [[Everthorpe]], (near [[Brough, East Riding of Yorkshire|Brough]]) in the [[East Riding of Yorkshire]], [[England]]. The prison was operated by [[Her Majesty's Prison Service]], and was situated next to [[Wolds (HM Prison)|HMP Wolds]].\n\nIn 2014, HM Prison Everthorpe was merged with HM Prison Wolds, and renamed [[HM Prison Humber]].\n\n==History==\nOriginally a [[borstal]] at its creation in 1958, in 1991 Everthorpe Prison was converted to house male convicts.\n\nDuring the Christmas and New Year period of 1995/1996, Everthorpe experienced some prisoner unrest that resulted in a large, two-day prison [[riot]]. According to investigators, the unrest was caused by official steps to eliminate drug use by inmates and also by shortages of tobacco and phonecards, which had run out over the holiday period. The prison was criticised for its lack of security, bad management and the deployment of inexperienced staff during the riot.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20121022035442/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-4774972.html HighBeam]</ref>\n\nAn inspection report from the [[Her Majesty's Chief Inspector of Prisons]] in July 2004 praised Everthorpe Prison for its education and training programmes, but warned that Everthorpe needed to ensure that all inmates at the prison benefitted from these programmes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/humber/3871703.stm |title=UK &#124; England &#124; Humber &#124; Jail 'must make more of training' |publisher=BBC News |date=2004-07-07 |accessdate=2013-04-12}}</ref>\n\nThe prison was substantially expanded in 2005. In an inspection report a year later, Everthorpe was criticised by the Chief Inspector of Prisons because places on resettlement and offending behaviour programmes had \"failed to keep pace\" with the increased number of prisoners held at the prison.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/humber/5338036.stm |title=UK &#124; England &#124; Humber &#124; Prison 'needs to support inmates' |publisher=BBC News |date=2006-09-12 |accessdate=2013-04-12}}</ref> The report also highlighted problems with bullying amongst inmates.\n\nIn January 2008 it emerged that inmates at Everthorpe had been regularly smuggling drugs, mobile phones and women's clothing into the prison. A ladder had been used by an accomplice on the outside to scale the 20-foot perimeter wall of the prison to supply these items, with the racket reportedly continuing for at least six months.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,321686,00.html |title=U.K. Transvestite's Friend Uses Ladder to Scale Prison Wall, Deliver Women's Clothes |publisher=Fox News |date= |accessdate=2013-04-12}}</ref>\n\n==The prison==\nEverthorpe was a Category C training prison with a strong emphasis of on education and training. Education at Everthorpe was provided by [[The Manchester College]] and [[East Riding College]] with courses including [[Literacy]], [[Numeracy]], [[Art and Design]], [[Information Technology]], [[Business]], [[wall and floor tiling]], [[Painting and Decorating]], [[Bricklaying]], Industrial [[cleaner|cleaning]], and [[Computer Aided Design]]. The PE department at the prison also ran various [[Physical Education]] courses as well as recreational gym.\n\nIt was announced in June 2013 that HM Prisons Everthorpe and Wolds would merge into one larger prison under a new name: [[HM Prison Humber]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.justice.gov.uk/global/contacts/noms/prison-finder/everthorpe/ Ministry of Justice Pages on Everthorpe]\n* [http://prizzonor.tumblr.com/post/80249855686/a-memorable-moral-moment A Memorable Moral Moment] -- redemptive memories of Everthorpe by an ex-inmate\n* [http://www.justiceinspectorates.gov.uk/hmiprisons/inspections/?s&location=everthorpe HMP Everthorpe - HM Inspectorate of Prisons Reports]\n\n{{coord|53.7682|-0.6351|type:landmark_region:GB|display=title}}\n\n{{Prisons in Yorkshire and the Humber}}\n\n[[Category:Category C prisons in England|Everthorpe]]\n[[Category:Prisons in the East Riding of Yorkshire|Everthorpe]]\n[[Category:1958 establishments in England]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox prison\n| prison_name    = HMP Everthorpe\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| location       = [[Everthorpe]], [[East Riding of Yorkshire]]\n| coordinates    = \n| status         = \n| classification = [[Prisoner security categories in the United Kingdom|Adult Male/Category C]]\n| capacity       = \n| population     = 689\n| populationdate = December 2007\n| opened         = 1958\n| closed         = \n| former_name    =\n| managed_by     = [[Her Majesty's Prison Service|HM Prison Services]]\n| governor       = Marcella Goligher\n| website        = {{HM prison|everthorpe|Everthorpe}}\n}}\n'''HM Prison Everthorpe''' was a [[Prison security categories in the United Kingdom|Category C]] men's [[prison]], located to the south-west of [[Everthorpe]], (near [[Brough, East Riding of Yorkshire|Brough]]) in the [[East Riding of Yorkshire]], [[England]]. The prison was operated by [[Her Majesty's Prison Service]], and was situated next to [[Wolds (HM Prison)|HMP Wolds]].\n\nIn 2014, HM Prison Everthorpe was merged with HM Prison Wolds, and renamed [[HM Prison Humber]].\n\n==History==\nOriginally a [[borstal]] at its creation in 1958, in 1991 Everthorpe Prison was converted to house male convicts.\n\nDuring the Christmas and New Year period of 1995/1996, Everthorpe experienced some prisoner unrest that resulted in a large, two-day prison [[riot]]. According to investigators, the unrest was caused by official steps to eliminate drug use by inmates and also by shortages of tobacco and phonecards, which had run out over the holiday period. The prison was criticised for its lack of security, bad management and the deployment of inexperienced staff during the riot.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20121022035442/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-4774972.html HighBeam]</ref>\n\nAn inspection report from the [[Her Majesty's Chief Inspector of Prisons]] in July 2004 praised Everthorpe Prison for its education and training programmes, but warned that Everthorpe needed to ensure that all inmates at the prison benefitted from these programmes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/humber/3871703.stm |title=UK &#124; England &#124; Humber &#124; Jail 'must make more of training' |publisher=BBC News |date=2004-07-07 |accessdate=2013-04-12}}</ref>\n\nThe prison was substantially expanded in 2005. In an inspection report a year later, Everthorpe was criticised by the Chief Inspector of Prisons because places on resettlement and offending behaviour programmes had \"failed to keep pace\" with the increased number of prisoners held at the prison.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/england/humber/5338036.stm |title=UK &#124; England &#124; Humber &#124; Prison 'needs to support inmates' |publisher=BBC News |date=2006-09-12 |accessdate=2013-04-12}}</ref> The report also highlighted problems with bullying amongst inmates.\n\nIn January 2008 it emerged that inmates at Everthorpe had been regularly smuggling drugs, mobile phones and women's clothing into the prison. A ladder had been used by an accomplice on the outside to scale the 20-foot perimeter wall of the prison to supply these items, with the racket reportedly continuing for at least six months.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,321686,00.html |title=U.K. Transvestite's Friend Uses Ladder to Scale Prison Wall, Deliver Women's Clothes |publisher=Fox News |date= |accessdate=2013-04-12}}</ref>\n\n==The prison==\nEverthorpe was a Category C training prison with a strong emphasis of on education and training. Education at Everthorpe was provided by [[The Manchester College]] and [[East Riding College]] with courses including [[Literacy]], [[Numeracy]], [[Art and Design]], [[Information Technology]], [[Business]], [[wall and floor tiling]], [[Painting and Decorating]], [[Bricklaying]], Industrial [[cleaner|cleaning]], and [[Computer Aided Design]]. The PE department at the prison also ran various [[Physical Education]] courses as well as recreational gym.\n\nIt was announced in June 2013 that HM Prisons Everthorpe and Wolds would merge into one larger prison under a new name: [[HMP Humber|HM Prison Humber]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.justice.gov.uk/global/contacts/noms/prison-finder/everthorpe/ Ministry of Justice Pages on Everthorpe]\n* [http://prizzonor.tumblr.com/post/80249855686/a-memorable-moral-moment A Memorable Moral Moment] -- redemptive memories of Everthorpe by an ex-inmate\n* [http://www.justiceinspectorates.gov.uk/hmiprisons/inspections/?s&location=everthorpe HMP Everthorpe - HM Inspectorate of Prisons Reports]\n\n{{coord|53.7682|-0.6351|type:landmark_region:GB|display=title}}\n\n{{Prisons in Yorkshire and the Humber}}\n\n[[Category:Category C prisons in England|Everthorpe]]\n[[Category:Prisons in the East Riding of Yorkshire|Everthorpe]]\n[[Category:1958 establishments in England]]\n", "name_user": "Paul W", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eThe prison:amend link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.or